<title>JAPAN: Imagineer shares fall sharply in afternoon Tokyo.</title>
<headline>Imagineer shares fall sharply in afternoon Tokyo.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-01-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in Imagineer Co Ltd fell sharply in afternoon trading in Tokyo on Wednesday following its share split annoucement the day before.</p>
<p>As of 0504 GMT, the shares were trading at 6,400 yen, down from Tuesday's close of 6,890 yen.</p>
<p>Imagineer said on Tuesday it planned a 1.2-for-1 share split on May 20, for shareholders as of March 31. It also said it planned a public offering of 800,000 shares and that the payment date was February 13.</p>
<p>&quot;The amount of the planned public offering was not that large, but the offering was taken as a selling factor given current weak demand as a whole,&quot; a trader said.</p>
